knitr document van Steensel lab

LAD rewiring data: CRISPRa in RPE cells – linking DamID changes to gene expession changes.

Bas van Steensel, Feb 2019.

Introduction

This script plots gene expression related figure panels of Brueckner et al.

Description of Data

  • DamID data preprocessed as in scripts LAD_Rewiring_RPE_CRISPRa_[.]*_BvS[0-9]{6}.Rhtml. Data are average smoothed DamID scores per gene.
  • Genome annotation is Ensembl build 75. This build is a bit old, but it is what the NKI Genomics Core Facility uses for RNAseq data processing.
  • Expression data for 8 targeted genes by Laura Brueckner. Two replicates each.

Path, Libraries, Parameters and Functions

#directory:
setwd("~/mydata/Projects/LADrewiring/")

#general stuff:
StartTime<-Sys.time() #used to determine runtime, see very end of this doc
Date<-substr(gsub("-", "", Sys.time()),3,8)

#libraries:
library(GenomicRanges)
library(data.table) #for fast reading of data files
library(Sushi) #for plotting gene annotations
library(ggplot2)
library(ggrepel)

#parameters:
#SMTH<-201 #smoothing window size (GATC fragments)
#NBrange<-2e6 #range over which we consider genes "neighbors"

#GN<-"CCSER1" #name of experiment (the gene(s) that was/were targeted), one of:
ExpList<-c("ctrl","ABCB1", "ADAM22", "CCSER1", "GRID2","MLK4", "PCNXL2", "PTN","SOX6")

#mygenes<-GN

Functions for loading, smoothing, domainogram calculation, and plotting

Gene annotation data

Load Refseq annotations and convert to bed format dataframe. The latter is needed for the plotting of gene tracks using the Sushi package.

#Ensembl hg19 build 75 downloaded from    feb2014.archive.ensembl.org/biomart/martview/4c34fe2f4e47c6b55a212cc95e3c952b
#load:
Ensembl.75<-read.delim("./data/ensEMBL/hg19/ensEMBL75_GRCh37.p13.txt", head=TRUE, sep="\t", as.is=TRUE)
#select and rename columns to make a .bed like dataframe:
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[,c(3,4,5,7,6,6,1)]
names(Ensembl.75)<-c("chrom", "start", "stop", "gene", "score","strand","ensembl.gene.id")
#only on full chromosomes:
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[Ensembl.75$chrom %in% c(1:22,"X","Y"),]
#reformat some stuff:
Ensembl.75$chrom<-paste0("chr",Ensembl.75$chrom)
Ensembl.75$strand<-ifelse(Ensembl.75$strand==-1, "-", "+")
#remove redundancies
Ensembl.75<-unique(Ensembl.75)
#remove questionable genes (mostly absent in UCSC):
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[-grep("^RP11", Ensembl.75$gene, value=FALSE),]
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[-grep("^AC[0-9]{6}[.][0-9]*", Ensembl.75$gene, value=FALSE),]
Ensembl.75<-Ensembl.75[Ensembl.75$stop - Ensembl.75$start > 200,] #remove very small genes, as the plotGenes() function of Sushi cannot cope with them
#how many genes in the end:
dim(Ensembl.75)

## [1] 34717     7

#as genomic ranges object:
GeneGR<-makeGRangesFromDataFrame(Ensembl.75)

#gene coordinates:
ggene<-c(); gchrom<-c(); gstart<-c(); gstop<-c()
for(g in ExpList[-1])
{wh<-which(Ensembl.75$gene==g)
 ggene[g]<-g
 gchrom[g]<-as.character(unique(Ensembl.75$chrom[wh]))
 gstart[g]<-min(c(Ensembl.75$start[wh],Ensembl.75$stop[wh]))
 gstop[g]<-max(c(Ensembl.75$start[wh],Ensembl.75$stop[wh]))
}
gchrom<-as.character(gchrom)
names(gchrom)<-ggene
print(data.frame(gene=ggene, chrom=gchrom, start=gstart, end=gstop))

Import, process, combine expression data. 

#code adapted from Laura (lb20180827_RPE_CRISPRa_quantdetach_correxpr_flanking_us.Rmd):
expdir<-c("/home/l.brueckner/mydata/figures_paper_rewiring/data/RPE_CRISPRa_fpkm/")
df<-(read.table(paste0(expdir,c("genes.fpkm_tracking_1502")),stringsAsFactors = F,header=T))[c("gene_id","gene_short_name","locus")]
df<-df[order(df$gene_id),]
fileslist<-list.files(path = expdir,pattern = "genes*")
FPKM_list<-lapply(fileslist,function(list){
  name<-substr(list,21,nchar(list))
  data<-read.table(paste0(expdir,list),stringsAsFactors = F,header=T)
  data<-data[order(data$gene_id),]
  return(data$FPKM)
  })
names<-lapply(fileslist,function(list)substr(list,21,nchar(list)))
FPKM_df<-data.frame(FPKM_list)
names(FPKM_df)<-unlist(names)
FPKM_df<-cbind(df,FPKM_df)

#focus on most informative gene set:
RNAseq<-FPKM_df[FPKM_df$gene_id %in% Ensembl.75$ensembl.gene.id,]

#merge with annotation:
RNAseq<-merge(Ensembl.75, RNAseq, by.x="ensembl.gene.id", by.y="gene_id")

#which RNAseq dataset belongs to which targeted gene:
ExS<-list()
ExS[["ctrl"]]<-c("1502","1502_r2")
ExS[["ABCB1"]]<-c("1503","1503_r2")
ExS[["ADAM22"]]<-c("187","187_r2")
ExS[["CCSER1"]]<-c("170","170_r2")
ExS[["GRID2"]]<-c("171","171_r2")
ExS[["MLK4"]]<-c("182","182_r2")
ExS[["PCNXL2"]]<-c("181","181_r2")
ExS[["PTN"]]<-c("162","162_r2")
ExS[["SOX6"]]<-c("163","163_r2")

#check if replicates correlate well:
for(i in ExpList)
  {print(paste(i,cor(RNAseq[,ExS[[i]]])[1,2]))}

Plot comparison of DamID and Expression data for targeted genes:

dDctl<-c()
dDexp<-c()
dEctl<-c()
dEexp<-c()
for(GN in ExpList[-1])
{load(paste0("LAD_rewiring_RPE_",GN,"_DamID_byGene_MeanSmoothed201_BvS190218.Rdata"))
 dDctl[GN]<-DamIDbyGene[DamIDbyGene$gene==GN,"DamID.ctl.mean"]
 dDexp[GN]<-DamIDbyGene[DamIDbyGene$gene==GN,"DamID.exp.mean"]
 dEctl[GN]<-RNAseq[RNAseq$gene==GN,"ctrl"]
 dEexp[GN]<-RNAseq[RNAseq$gene==GN,GN]
}
DvsE<-data.frame(DamID=c(dDctl,dDexp),
                 Expr=log2(c(dEctl,dEexp)+0.1), #0.1 pseudocount
                 sample=c(rep("control",length(dEctl)),rep("experimental",length(dEexp))),
                 gene=rep(ExpList[-1],2))
cor.test(DvsE$Expr, DvsE$DamID, method="spearman")

## 
##  Spearman's rank correlation rho
## 
## data:  DvsE$Expr and DvsE$DamID
## S = 1239.4, p-value = 9.125e-05
## alternative hypothesis: true rho is not equal to 0
## sample estimates:
##        rho 
## -0.8226639

#plot:
ggplot(DvsE,aes(x=Expr,y=DamID,col=sample,label=gene))+
  scale_color_manual(values=c("navy","darkred"))+
  xlab(expression("RNA-seq log"[2]*"(FPKM)"))+
  ylab(expression("log"[2]*"(DamID ratio)"))+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_smooth(aes(x=Expr,y=DamID), method="lm", inherit.aes = FALSE, col="#666666", lty="dashed")+
  geom_text_repel()+
  geom_point()+
  theme(legend.position = c(0.9, 0.9))+
  theme(legend.text=element_text(size=rel(1.2)),
        axis.text=element_text(size=rel(1.2)),
        axis.title=element_text(size=rel(1.2)))


pdf(file=paste0("LAD_Rewiring_RPE_Expression_vs_DamID_scatter_BvS",Date,".pdf"), width=6, height=6)
ggplot(DvsE,aes(x=Expr,y=DamID,col=sample,label=gene))+
  scale_color_manual(values=c("navy","darkred"))+
  xlab(expression("RNA-seq log"[2]*"(FPKM)"))+
  ylab(expression("log"[2]*"(DamID ratio)"))+
  theme_bw()+
  geom_smooth(aes(x=Expr,y=DamID), method="lm", inherit.aes = FALSE, col="#666666", lty="dashed")+
  geom_text_repel()+
  geom_point()+
  theme(legend.position = c(0.9, 0.9))+
  theme(legend.text=element_text(size=rel(1.2)),
        axis.text=element_text(size=rel(1.2)),
        axis.title=element_text(size=rel(1.2)))
dev.off() #close PDF
